  "name": "Clopidogrel Poor Metabolizers",
  "description": "This test case evaluates the ability to identify a complex pharmacogenomic phenotype for clopidogrel poor metabolizers. It requires finding patients who received coronary stents and then had adverse events (MI, stroke, revascularization) that suggest inadequate antiplatelet response to clopidogrel therapy. The phenotype involves multiple resource types including procedures (stent placement, CABG), conditions (MI, stroke), and requires temporal relationships between events.",
  "prompt": "Find patients who had coronary stent placement and subsequently experienced adverse cardiovascular events like myocardial infarction, stroke, or need for revascularization procedures, indicating they may be poor metabolizers of clopidogrel.",
